data.title: Aaryn Doyle - Age, Family, Bio
data.meta_description: Aaryn Doyle: her birthday, what she did before fame, her family life, fun trivia facts, popularity rankings, and more.
data.text:
About

Notable as the voice of Foo in the animated television series The Save-Ums!, Doyle also voiced characters in Miss Spider's Sunny Patch Friends (Pansy) and Friends and Heroes (Flore). Also a live action performer, she portrayed Lola in the 2008 made-for-TV movie Camp Rock.

Before Fame

She made her screen acting debut in a 2002 TV movie titled Sins of the Father.

Trivia

A model as well as a voiceover artist and actress, she appeared in advertising campaigns for the Nike and Diesel athletic brands.

Family Life

Born and raised in Ontario, Canada, she is of West Indian, Jewish, and Irish descent.
